![Mobile settings screen](https://github.com/xlabtg/Teleton-Client/blob/issue-135-0f2d02a22cbb/docs/screenshots/web-alpha-settings-mobile.png?raw=true)

## Tests
- `cd web && npm install`
- `cd web && npm run test`
- `cd web && npm run build`
- `npm test`
- `npm run validate:secrets`
- `npm run audit:security`
- `npm run validate:foundation`
- `npm run validate:release`
- `npm run build:debug-artifacts`
- `npm run decompose:dry-run`
- Playwright preview check at `http://localhost:4173/app/` for desktop and mobile screenshots

## Risk / Follow-Up
- Live Telegram auth and messaging require valid `VITE_TELEGRAM_API_ID` and `VITE_TELEGRAM_API_HASH` plus TDWeb runtime assets copied by `npm install`.
- `npm audit --omit=dev` in `web/` reports two moderate findings inherited from `tdweb@1.8.0 -> uuid`, with no upstream fix available from `tdweb` today. This is documented in `web/README.md` for release review.
- Browser access to the agent Management API may require local TLS/CORS configuration because the current agent API uses self-signed HTTPS on `localhost:7778`.

